.geogratis.gc.ca", "resource_type": "file", "language": "eng; CAN", "format": "other"}, {"url": "www.geogratis.gc.ca", "resource_type": "file", "language": "eng; CAN", "format": "other"}, {"url": "http://ftp2.cits.rncan.gc.ca/pub/canmatrix/50k_300dpi/068/g/canmatrix_068g08_tif.zip", "resource_type": "file", "language": "eng; CAN", "format": "other"}, {"url": "ftp://ftp2.cits.rncan.gc.ca/pub/canmatrix/50k_300dpi/068/g/canmatrix_068g08_tif.zip", "resource_type": "file", "language": "eng; CAN", "format": "other"}, {"url": "www.geogratis.gc.ca", "resource_type": "file", "language": "eng; CAN", "format": "other"}], "browse_graphic_url": "http://www.fakeimageurl123.com/foo.jpg", "topic_category": "Imagery Base Maps Earth Cover  Imagerie carte de base couverture terrestre", "tags": [], "endpoint_url_fra": "http://geogratis.gc.ca/api/fr/nrcan-rncan/ess-sst/", "date_published": "2010-11-02", "time_period_coverage_start": "1958-01-01", "data_series_name": "CanMatrix - georeferenced", "endpoint_url": "http://geogratis.gc.ca/api/en/nrcan-rncan/ess-sst/", "time_period_coverage_end": "1958-01-01", "notes": "This CanMatrix (georeferenced) file is composed of raster data from scanned the map at the 1:50 000 scale. The source of this raster file (paper map) is geocoded according to the North American Datum of 1927 (NAD27) with May 1976 Adjustment.  The resulting raster file is georeferenced to the North American Datum of 1983 (NAD 83) according to the Universal Transverse Mercator (UTM) projection. This product is distributed in GeoTIFF.  The Centre for Topographic Information wants to create a national database composed of raster map data where each pixel has a distinct geographic location (georeferenced data).", "title": "CanMatrix - georeferenced - 068G08", "keywords_fra": "Canmatrix-068g08-1.0,Sciences de la terre,B\u00e2timents,Communications,Altitude du relief,Lacs,Utilisation - couverture des terres,Rivi\u00e8res - cours d-eau,Transport,Nunavut,Hooker bay,068g08", "organizati